
// This Hyperlambda code checks the value of the [.flag] node. If the value evaluates to true, it sets the value of the [.result] node to "The condition is true". The [if] slot is used to conditionally execute the [set-value] operation based on the evaluation of the [get-value] slot.
if
   get-value:x:@.flag
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.result
         .:The condition is true
